      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE WHIPPET (1) registered a strong performance last start when he battled on bravely to just miss out over 1609m at Charlton. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Good enough to put himself in the winners' stall. BETTOR BE BODHI (7) is racing well with six top-five finishes in succession, the latest effort a third at Albion Park over 1660m. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Won't find this any harder and he can add to the impressive recent record. KEAYANG KAUNA (9) ended last prep with a fifth at Albury over 1770m five months ago. Capable of a forward showing while fresh. DIGBY DEVIL (3) is next best and gets every chance from a favourable draw.",
